# Semgrep path exclusions — keep `semgrep scan --config auto` (see
# .github/workflows/security.yml) focused on the PRODUCTION attack surface.
#
# Test/E2E specs, one-off POC scripts, and the Shipwright SDLC doc tree are
# not shipped at runtime; scanning them only produced audit-rule noise that
# GitHub code-scanning then inflated to "high" (111 high / 19 medium), while
# the dashboard ingest graded the same findings "low" — the divergence that
# triage item trg-4c0ab9b0 surfaced. Production-code false positives are
# suppressed inline with `// nosemgrep: <rule>` + a justification comment.
# See iterate-2026-06-30-semgrep-fp-suppression.

# --- Test + E2E suites (Vitest unit/integration + Playwright) ---
*.test.ts
*.test.tsx
*.spec.ts
*.spec.tsx
client/e2e/

# --- One-off / POC scripts (not part of the runtime server or client) ---
server/scripts/

# --- Shipwright SDLC docs, planning, compliance artifacts (not code) ---
.shipwright/

# --- Build output / vendored deps (node_modules is default-ignored; explicit) ---
dist/
build/
node_modules/
